The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 AFI under scanner

New Delhi: The Athletics Federation of India (AFI) on Monday came under the scanner after more light thrown on the S. Shanti gender controversy revealed that it had been aware all through of the athlete not possessing female characteristics. 

According to a top official, part of the Indian contingent in Doha, Shanti had failed a gender test conducted by the Railways medical board when she had applied for a job. 

The AFI was aware about it and still decided to take a chance considering that the athlete had successfully competed in some other international meets, the official said. 

Meanwhile, the Indian Olympic Association on Monday confirmed that S. Shanti had failed the gender verification test and has been stripped of her Doha Asian Games 800m silver medal. (PTI) 




